text: Kimberly Jess (born 30 January 1992) is a former German high jumper and occasionally participated in long jump events in international level events. She was a junior World champion in the 2008 World Junior Championships in Athletics in Bydgoszcz, Poland. ==References== Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:People from Rendsburg Category:German female high jumpers
